Power.description: Can be read to return if the device is correctly powered or not, set via the power system, return 1 if powered and 0 if not

Mode.description: Integer for mode state, different devices will have different mode states available to them

Error.description: 1 if device is in error state, otherwise 0

Temperature.description: The current temperature reading of the device

PressureExternal.description: Setting for external pressure safety, in KPa. Represents the target pressure of the external atmosphere.

PressureInternal.description: Setting for internal pressure safety, in KPa. Represents the target pressure of the atmosphere inside the connected pipe network.

Activate.description: 1 if device is activated (usually means running), otherwise 0

Lock.description: 1 if device is locked, otherwise 0, can be set in most devices and prevents the user from access the values

Color.description:
Whether driven by concerns for clarity, safety or simple aesthetics, Stationeers have access to a small rainbow of colors for their constructions. These are the color setting for devices, represented as an integer.

0: Blue
1: Grey
2: Green
3: Orange
4: Red
5: Yellow
6: White
7: Black
8: Brown
9: Khaki
10: Pink
11: Purple

        It is an unwavering universal law that anything higher than 11 will be purple. The ODA is powerless to change this. Similarly, anything lower than 0 will be Blue.

Progress.description: Progress of the rocket to the next node on the map expressed as a value between 0-1.

DestinationCode.description: The Space Map Address of the rockets target Space Map Location

Acceleration.description: Change in velocity. Rockets that are deccelerating when landing will show this as negative value.

ReferenceId.description: Unique Reference Identifier for this object

AutoShutOff.description: Turns off all devices in the rocket upon reaching destination

Mass.description: The total Mass of the rocket in kilograms including fuel and cargo. The more massive the rocket the more fuel will be required to move to a new location in space.

DryMass.description: The Mass in kilograms of the rocket excluding fuel. The more massive the rocket the more fuel will be required to move to a new location in space.

Thrust.description: Total current thrust of all rocket engines on the rocket in Newtons.

Weight.description: Weight of Rocket in Newtons (Including fuel and cargo). Weight is effected by local body gravity.

ThrustToWeight.description: Ratio of thrust to weight of rocket. Weight is effected by local body gravity. A rocket with a low thrust to weight will expend more fuel during launch and landing.

TimeToDestination.description: Estimated time in seconds until rocket arrives at target destination.

BurnTimeRemaining.description: Estimated time in seconds until fuel is depleted. Calculated based on current fuel usage.

AutoLand.description: Engages the automatic landing algorithm. The rocket will automatically throttle and turn on and off its engines to achieve a smooth landing.

ForwardX.description: The direction the entity is facing expressed as a normalized vector

ForwardY.description: The direction the entity is facing expressed as a normalized vector

ForwardZ.description: The direction the entity is facing expressed as a normalized vector

Orientation.description: The orientation of the entity in degrees in a plane relative towards the north origin

VelocityX.description: The world velocity of the entity in the X axis

VelocityY.description: The world velocity of the entity in the Y axis

VelocityZ.description: The world velocity of the entity in the Z axis

PassedMoles.description: The number of moles that passed through this device on the previous simulation tick

ExhaustVelocity.description: The velocity of the exhaust gas in m/s

FlightControlRule.description: Flight control rule of rocket. None = 0, No AutoPilot. Normal = 1, Target Decent Apex of 60m. Alternate = 2, Velocity to High - Full throttle. Alternate2 = 3, Target an appropriate decent velocity as velocity is too low. FinalApproach = 4, Descend towards launch mount in a controlled manner.

ReEntryAltitude.description: The altitude that the rocket will begin its decent to the pad. Must be between 25km and 120km

Apex.description: The lowest altitude that the rocket will reach before it starts travelling upwards again.

EntityState.description: The current entity state, such as whether it is dead, unconscious or alive, expressed as a state integer.

DrillCondition.description: The current condition of the drill head in this devices drill slot. Expressed as a ratio between 0 and 1.

Index.description: The current index for the device.

CelestialHash.description: The current hash of the targeted celestial object.

AlignmentError.description: The angular discrepancy between the telescope's current orientation and the target. Indicates how 'off target' the telescope is. Returns NaN when no target.

DistanceAu.description: The current distance to the celestial object, measured in astronomical units.

OrbitPeriod.description: The time it takes for an object to complete one full orbit around another object, measured in days. Indicates the duration of the orbital cycle.

Inclination.description: The tilt of an orbit's plane relative to the equatorial plane, measured in degrees. Defines the orbital plane's angle.

Eccentricity.description: A measure of how elliptical (oval) an orbit is. Ranges from 0 (a perfect circle) to 1 (a parabolic trajectory).

SemiMajorAxis.description: The longest radius of an elliptical orbit in astronomical units, measuring half the major axis. Determines the size of the orbit.

DistanceKm.description: The current distance to the celestial object, measured in kilometers.

CelestialParentHash.description: The hash for the name of the parent the celestial is orbiting, 0 if there is no parent celestial.

TrueAnomaly.description: An angular parameter that defines the position of a body moving along a Keplerian orbit. It is the angle between the direction of periapsis and the current position of the body, as seen from the main focus of the ellipse (the point around which the object orbits).

RatioHydrogen.description: The ratio of Hydrogen in device's Atmopshere

RatioLiquidHydrogen.description: The ratio of Liquid Hydrogen in device's Atmopshere

RatioPollutedWater.description: The ratio of polluted water in device atmosphere

Discover.description: Progress status of Discovery scan at the rocket's target Space Map Location. Returns a clamped normalised value. If Discovery scan is not available returns -1.

Chart.description: Progress status of Chart scan at the rocket's target Space Map Location. Returns a clamped normalised value. If Chart scan is not available returns -1.

Survey.description: Progress status of Survey scan at the rocket's target Space Map Location. Returns a normalised value where 100% surveyed is equal to 1. If Survey scan is not available returns -1.

NavPoints.description: The number of NavPoints at the rocket's target Space Map Location.

ChartedNavPoints.description: The number of charted NavPoints at the rocket's target Space Map Location.

Sites.description: The number of Sites that have been discovered at the rockets target Space Map location.

CurrentCode.description: The Space Map Address of the rockets current Space Map Location

Density.description: The density of the rocket's target site's mine-able deposit.

Richness.description: The richness of the rocket's target site's mine-able deposit.

Size.description: The size of the rocket's target site's mine-able deposit.

TotalQuantity.description: The estimated total quantity of resources available to mine at the rocket's target Space Map Site.

MinedQuantity.description: The total number of resources that have been mined at the rocket's target Space Map Site.

BestContactFilter.description: Filters the satellite's auto selection of targets to a single reference ID.

NameHash.description: Provides the hash value for the name of the object as a 32 bit integer.

Altitude.description: The altitude that the rocket above the planet's surface. -1 if the rocket is in space.

TargetSlotIndex.description: The slot index that the target device that this device will try to interact with

NetworkFault.description: Attached network is experiencing a fault, such as a pipe burst or other failure.

ProportionalGain.description: The proportional gain of the PID controller. This value determines how aggressively the controller responds to the error between the setpoint and the process variable. A higher value results in a faster response but may lead to overshoot or instability.

IntegralGain.description: The integral gain of the PID controller. This value determines how much the controller responds to the accumulated error over time. A higher value can help eliminate steady-state errors but may also lead to oscillations or instability.

DerivativeGain.description: The derivative gain of the PID controller. This value determines how much the controller responds to the rate of change of the error. A higher value can help dampen oscillations and improve stability, but may also lead to noise amplification.

Minimum.description: Minimum value for provided logic device.

Setpoint.description: The desired value that the PID controller aims to achieve. This is the target value for the process variable, and the controller will adjust its output to minimize the difference between the setpoint and the process variable.

Reset.description: Resets the PID controller's internal state, clearing any accumulated error and resetting the output to zero. This is useful for starting fresh or recovering from an unstable state.

Progress.description: Progress of the rocket to the next node on the map expressed as a value between 0-1.

DestinationCode.description: The Space Map Address of the rockets target Space Map Location

Acceleration.description: Change in velocity. Rockets that are deccelerating when landing will show this as negative value.

ReferenceId.description: Unique Reference Identifier for this object

AutoShutOff.description: Turns off all devices in the rocket upon reaching destination

Mass.description: The total Mass of the rocket in kilograms including fuel and cargo. The more massive the rocket the more fuel will be required to move to a new location in space.

DryMass.description: The Mass in kilograms of the rocket excluding fuel. The more massive the rocket the more fuel will be required to move to a new location in space.

Thrust.description: Total current thrust of all rocket engines on the rocket in Newtons.

Weight.description: Weight of Rocket in Newtons (Including fuel and cargo). Weight is effected by local body gravity.

ThrustToWeight.description: Ratio of thrust to weight of rocket. Weight is effected by local body gravity. A rocket with a low thrust to weight will expend more fuel during launch and landing.

TimeToDestination.description: Estimated time in seconds until rocket arrives at target destination.

BurnTimeRemaining.description: Estimated time in seconds until fuel is depleted. Calculated based on current fuel usage.

AutoLand.description: Engages the automatic landing algorithm. The rocket will automatically throttle and turn on and off its engines to achieve a smooth landing.

ForwardX.description: The direction the entity is facing expressed as a normalized vector

ForwardY.description: The direction the entity is facing expressed as a normalized vector

ForwardZ.description: The direction the entity is facing expressed as a normalized vector

Orientation.description: The orientation of the entity in degrees in a plane relative towards the north origin

VelocityX.description: The world velocity of the entity in the X axis

VelocityY.description: The world velocity of the entity in the Y axis

VelocityZ.description: The world velocity of the entity in the Z axis

PassedMoles.description: The number of moles that passed through this device on the previous simulation tick

ExhaustVelocity.description: The velocity of the exhaust gas in m/s

FlightControlRule.description: Flight control rule of rocket. None = 0, No AutoPilot. Normal = 1, Target Decent Apex of 60m. Alternate = 2, Velocity to High - Full throttle. Alternate2 = 3, Target an appropriate decent velocity as velocity is too low. FinalApproach = 4, Descend towards launch mount in a controlled manner.

ReEntryAltitude.description: The altitude that the rocket will begin its decent to the pad. Must be between 25km and 120km

Apex.description: The lowest altitude that the rocket will reach before it starts travelling upwards again.

EntityState.description: The current entity state, such as whether it is dead, unconscious or alive, expressed as a state integer.

DrillCondition.description: The current condition of the drill head in this devices drill slot. Expressed as a ratio between 0 and 1.

Index.description: The current index for the device.

CelestialHash.description: The current hash of the targeted celestial object.

AlignmentError.description: The angular discrepancy between the telescope's current orientation and the target. Indicates how 'off target' the telescope is. Returns NaN when no target.

DistanceAu.description: The current distance to the celestial object, measured in astronomical units.

OrbitPeriod.description: The time it takes for an object to complete one full orbit around another object, measured in days. Indicates the duration of the orbital cycle.

Inclination.description: The tilt of an orbit's plane relative to the equatorial plane, measured in degrees. Defines the orbital plane's angle.

Eccentricity.description: A measure of how elliptical (oval) an orbit is. Ranges from 0 (a perfect circle) to 1 (a parabolic trajectory).

SemiMajorAxis.description: The longest radius of an elliptical orbit in astronomical units, measuring half the major axis. Determines the size of the orbit.

DistanceKm.description: The current distance to the celestial object, measured in kilometers.

CelestialParentHash.description: The hash for the name of the parent the celestial is orbiting, 0 if there is no parent celestial.

TrueAnomaly.description: An angular parameter that defines the position of a body moving along a Keplerian orbit. It is the angle between the direction of periapsis and the current position of the body, as seen from the main focus of the ellipse (the point around which the object orbits).

RatioHydrogen.description: The ratio of Hydrogen in device's Atmopshere

RatioLiquidHydrogen.description: The ratio of Liquid Hydrogen in device's Atmopshere

RatioPollutedWater.description: The ratio of polluted water in device atmosphere

Discover.description: Progress status of Discovery scan at the rocket's target Space Map Location. Returns a clamped normalised value. If Discovery scan is not available returns -1.

Chart.description: Progress status of Chart scan at the rocket's target Space Map Location. Returns a clamped normalised value. If Chart scan is not available returns -1.

Survey.description: Progress status of Survey scan at the rocket's target Space Map Location. Returns a normalised value where 100% surveyed is equal to 1. If Survey scan is not available returns -1.

NavPoints.description: The number of NavPoints at the rocket's target Space Map Location.

ChartedNavPoints.description: The number of charted NavPoints at the rocket's target Space Map Location.

Sites.description: The number of Sites that have been discovered at the rockets target Space Map location.

CurrentCode.description: The Space Map Address of the rockets current Space Map Location

Density.description: The density of the rocket's target site's mine-able deposit.

Richness.description: The richness of the rocket's target site's mine-able deposit.

Size.description: The size of the rocket's target site's mine-able deposit.

TotalQuantity.description: The estimated total quantity of resources available to mine at the rocket's target Space Map Site.

MinedQuantity.description: The total number of resources that have been mined at the rocket's target Space Map Site.

BestContactFilter.description: Filters the satellite's auto selection of targets to a single reference ID.

NameHash.description: Provides the hash value for the name of the object as a 32 bit integer.

Altitude.description: The altitude that the rocket above the planet's surface. -1 if the rocket is in space.

TargetSlotIndex.description: The slot index that the target device that this device will try to interact with

NetworkFault.description: Attached network is experiencing a fault, such as a pipe burst or other failure.

ProportionalGain.description: The proportional gain of the PID controller. This value determines how aggressively the controller responds to the error between the setpoint and the process variable. A higher value results in a faster response but may lead to overshoot or instability.

IntegralGain.description: The integral gain of the PID controller. This value determines how much the controller responds to the accumulated error over time. A higher value can help eliminate steady-state errors but may also lead to oscillations or instability.

DerivativeGain.description: The derivative gain of the PID controller. This value determines how much the controller responds to the rate of change of the error. A higher value can help dampen oscillations and improve stability, but may also lead to noise amplification.

Minimum.description: Minimum value for provided logic device.

Setpoint.description: The desired value that the PID controller aims to achieve. This is the target value for the process variable, and the controller will adjust its output to minimize the difference between the setpoint and the process variable.

Reset.description: Resets the PID controller's internal state, clearing any accumulated error and resetting the output to zero. This is useful for starting fresh or recovering from an unstable state.

StackSize.description: Returns the stack size of the devices internal memory.

Occupied.description: returns 0 when slot is not occupied, 1 when it is

OccupantHash.description: returns the hash of the current occupant, the unique identifier of the thing

Quantity.description: returns the current quantity, such as stack size, of the item in the slot

Damage.description: returns the damage state of the item in the slot

Efficiency.description: returns the growth efficiency of the plant in the slot

Health.description: Returns the health of the plant in the slot

Growth.description: returns the current growth state of the plant in the slot

Pressure.description: returns pressure of the slot occupants internal atmosphere

Temperature.description: returns temperature of the slot occupants internal atmosphere

Charge.description: returns current energy charge the slot occupant is holding

ChargeRatio.description: returns current energy charge the slot occupant is holding as a ratio between 0 and 1 of its maximum

Class.description: returns integer representing the class of object

PressureWaste.description: returns pressure in the waste tank of the jetpack in this slot

PressureAir.description: returns pressure in the air tank of the jetpack in this slot

MaxQuantity.description: returns the max stack size of the item in the slot

Mature.description: returns 1 if the plant in this slot is mature, 0 when it isn't

PrefabHash.description: returns the hash of the structure in the slot

Seeding.description: Whether a plant is seeding (ready to harvest seeds from). Returns 1 if seeding or 0 if not.

LineNumber.description: The line number of current execution for an integrated circuit running on this device. While this number can be written, use with caution

ReferenceId.description: Unique Reference Identifier for this object

MaturityRatio.description: How far the plant is towards maturity represented as a fraction between 0 and 1, with 1 being mature and ready for harvest.

SeedingRatio.description: How far the plant is towards seeding represented as a fraction between 0 and 1, with 1 being seeding and will supply seeds when harvested.

l.desc: Loads device LogicType to register by housing index value.

s.desc: Stores register value to LogicType on device by housing index value.

ls.desc: Loads slot LogicSlotType on device to register.

lr.desc: Loads reagent of device's ReagentMode where a hash of the reagent type to check for. ReagentMode can be either Contents (0), Required (1), Recipe (2). Can use either the word, or the number.

sb.desc: Stores register value to LogicType on all output network devices with provided type hash.

lb.desc: Loads LogicType from all output network devices with provided type hash using the provide batch mode. Average (0), Sum (1), Minimum (2), Maximum (3). Can use either the word, or the number.

alias.desc: Labels register or device reference with name, device references also affect what shows on the screws on the IC base.

move.desc: Register = provided num or register value.

sdse.desc: Register = 1 if device is set, otherwise 0.

sdns.desc: Register = 1 if device is not set, otherwise 0

sap.desc: Register = 1 if abs(a - b) <= max(c * max(abs(a), abs(b)), float.epsilon * 8), otherwise 0

sna.desc: Register = 1 if abs(a - b) > max(c * max(abs(a), abs(b)), float.epsilon * 8), otherwise 0

and.desc: Performs a bitwise logical AND operation on the binary representation of two values. Each bit of the result is determined by evaluating the corresponding bits of the input values. If both bits are 1, the resulting bit is set to 1. Otherwise the resulting bit is set to 0.

or.desc: Performs a bitwise logical OR operation on the binary representation of two values. Each bit of the result is determined by evaluating the corresponding bits of the input values. If either bit is 1, the resulting bit is set to 1. If both bits are 0, the resulting bit is set to 0.

xor.desc: Performs a bitwise logical XOR (exclusive OR) operation on the binary representation of two values. Each bit of the result is determined by evaluating the corresponding bits of the input values. If the bits are different (one bit is 0 and the other is 1), the resulting bit is set to 1. If the bits are the same (both 0 or both 1), the resulting bit is set to 0.

nor.desc: Performs a bitwise logical NOR (NOT OR) operation on the binary representation of two values. Each bit of the result is determined by evaluating the corresponding bits of the input values. If both bits are 0, the resulting bit is set to 1. Otherwise, if at least one bit is 1, the resulting bit is set to 0.

mod.desc: Register = a mod b (note: NOT a % b)

bltz.desc: Branch to line b if a < 0

bgez.desc: Branch to line b if a >= 0

blez.desc: Branch to line b if a <= 0

bgtz.desc: Branch to line b if a > 0

bdns.desc: Branch to line a if device d isn't set

beq.desc: Branch to line c if a == b

bne.desc: Branch to line c if a != b

bna.desc: Branch to line d if abs(a - b) > max(c * max(abs(a), abs(b)), float.epsilon * 8)

brgez.desc: Relative branch to line b if a >= 0

brgtz.desc: Relative branch to line b if a > 0

ble.desc: Branch to line c if a <= b

bge.desc: Branch to line c if a >= b

brge.desc: Relative jump to line c if a >= b

define.desc: Creates a label that will be replaced throughout the program with the provided value.

sleep.desc: Pauses execution on the IC for a seconds

sin.desc: Returns the sine of the specified angle (radians)

asin.desc: Returns the angle (radians) whos sine is the specified value

tan.desc: Returns the tan of the specified angle (radians)

atan.desc: Returns the angle (radians) whos tan is the specified value

cos.desc: Returns the cosine of the specified angle (radians)

acos.desc: Returns the cosine of the specified angle (radians)

atan2.desc: Returns the angle (radians) whose tangent is the quotient of two specified values: a (y) and b (x)

brnan.desc: Relative branch to line b if a is not a number (NaN)

bnan.desc: Branch to line b if a is not a number (NaN)

snan.desc: Register = 1 if a is NaN, otherwise 0

snanz.desc: Register = 0 if a is NaN, otherwise 1

lbs.desc: Loads LogicSlotType from slotIndex from all output network devices with provided type hash using the provide batch mode. Average (0), Sum (1), Minimum (2), Maximum (3). Can use either the word, or the number.
lbs.example: lbs r? deviceHash slotIndex logicSlotType batchMode

lbn.desc: Loads LogicType from all output network devices with provided type and name hashes using the provide batch mode. Average (0), Sum (1), Minimum (2), Maximum (3). Can use either the word, or the number.
lbn.example: lbn r? deviceHash nameHash logicType batchMode

sbn.desc: Stores register value to LogicType on all output network devices with provided type hash and name.

lbns.desc: Loads LogicSlotType from slotIndex from all output network devices with provided type and name hashes using the provide batch mode. Average (0), Sum (1), Minimum (2), Maximum (3). Can use either the word, or the number.
lbns.example: lbns r? deviceHash nameHash slotIndex logicSlotType batchMode

ss.desc: Stores register value to device stored in a slot LogicSlotType on device.

sbs.desc: Stores register value to LogicSlotType on all output network devices with provided type hash in the provided slot.

srl.desc: Performs a bitwise logical right shift operation on the binary representation of a value. It shifts the bits to the right and fills the vacated leftmost bits with zeros

sra.desc: Performs a bitwise arithmetic right shift operation on the binary representation of a value. It shifts the bits to the right and fills the vacated leftmost bits with a copy of the sign bit (the most significant bit).

sll.desc: Performs a bitwise logical left shift operation on the binary representation of a value. It shifts the bits to the left and fills the vacated rightmost bits with zeros.

sla.desc: Performs a bitwise arithmetic left shift operation on the binary representation of a value. It shifts the bits to the left and fills the vacated rightmost bits with a copy of the sign bit (the most significant bit).

not.desc: Performs a bitwise logical NOT operation flipping each bit of the input value, resulting in a binary complement. If a bit is 1, it becomes 0, and if a bit is 0, it becomes 1.

ld.desc: Loads device LogicType to register by direct ID reference.

sd.desc: Stores register value to LogicType on device by direct ID reference.

poke.desc: Stores the provided value at the provided address in the stack.

getd.desc: Seeks directly for the provided device id, attempts to read the stack value at the provided address, and places it in the register.

putd.desc: Seeks directly for the provided device id, attempts to write the provided value to the stack at the provided address.

get.desc: Using the provided device, attempts to read the stack value at the provided address, and places it in the register.

put.desc: Using the provided device, attempts to write the provided value to the stack at the provided address.

clr.desc: Clears the stack memory for the provided device.

clrd.desc: Seeks directly for the provided device id and clears the stack memory of that device

rmap.desc: Given a reagent hash, store the corresponding prefab hash that the device expects to fulfill the reagent requirement. For example, on an autolathe, the hash for Iron will store the hash for ItemIronIngot.

bdnvl.desc: Will branch to line a if the provided device not valid for a load instruction for the provided logic type.

bdnvs.desc: Will branch to line a if the provided device not valid for a store instruction for the provided logic type.

pow.desc: Stores the result of raising a to the power of b in the register. Follows IEEE-754 standard for floating point arithmetic.

ext.desc: Extracts a bit field from a, beginning at b for c length and placed in the provided register. Payload cannot exceed 53 bits in final length.

ins.desc: Inserts a bit field of a into the provided register, beginning at b for c length. Payload cannot exceed 53 bits in final length.

lerp.desc: Linearly interpolates between a and b by the ratio c, and places the result in the register provided. The ratio c will be clamped between 0 and 1.
